body.name: AsiaHorse 12VHPWR Cable Extension Kit, 16AWG Pcie 5.0 PSU Cable Extension Kit Soft Braided Power Supply Cable Extension, 24pin ATX /4+4pin EPS /12+4pin, 30CM Length with Cable Combs
deliveryMessages: FREE delivery Tuesday, February 20 on orders shipped by Amazon over $35
features: 【RTX 3090Ti/4070/4080/4090 PC Build Kit】Newest 12VHPWR Extension Cable Kit. Supports the latest RTX40 GPUs and allows for flexible extension of the original PSU cables to enhance wire routing.

【Upgrade Connector】The all-white precision combination connector effectively solves the problem of difficult connections in the market. It allows for easier connection of GPU and motherboard pins, eliminating concerns about small cable gaps that can make installation difficult.

【Extremely Soft】The motherboard and EPS cables have a 4mm diameter, offering a higher quality finish compared to standard 3.2mm cables. Notice: The 12vhpwr cable has a diameter of 2.5mm. Both cables adopt 16awg wires and a high-density braid, providing a balance between pliability and stiffness for the ideal cable routing solution.

【Support Ultra-high Performance Power Supply】The 12vhpwr extension is made of standard tinned copper wire and can support up to 600W output. This allows for easy handling of ultra-high-performance power supplies without any stress or worries of black screens and melted terminals, effectively protecting your graphics card.
【Package Includes】1 x 24-pin ATX Cable Extension, 2 x 4+4pin EPS, and 1 x 16pin(12+4) PCI-e Cable Extension. Each cable comes with 4 combs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great cable extension solution
reviews.reviewText: I recently completed my first build in a number of years, and wanted to put more effort into cable management than I had in previous attempts. I bought these to help counter the very stiff cables that came with my power supply, and over all I'm super happy with the purchase! The cables came packed super simple, just a standard cardboard box with very little in the way of documentation. The cable combs are also not preinstalled, and with 4+ combs per cable It does take a little time to get them all aligned, but the results are great. The cables look nice, and are way more flexible than the ones that came with the PSU. The one exception is the 12vhpwr cable, which again works great, but is still fairly stiff. I'd be careful to make sure that there's a decent amount of space between your graphics card and the wall of your case so that the cable isn't getting overly strained. Keeping that one demerit in mind, I'd still say that these are an easy 4.5/5 and would totally recommend!
